Module kivakit.core
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.time

Class Rate

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.core.time.Rate
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.function.Mapper<Long,Rate>, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.numeric.Maximizable<Rate>, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.numeric.Minimizable<Rate>, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.numeric.Zeroable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.value.DoubleValued, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.value.LongValued, Comparable<Rate>
public class Rate extends Object implements Comparable<Rate>, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.numeric.Maximizable<Rate>, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.numeric.Minimizable<Rate>, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.value.DoubleValued
An abstract rate in count per Duration. Rates can be constructed as a count per Duration with Rate(double, Duration) or with static factory methods:
  • perDay(double)
  • perHour(double)
  • perMinute(double)
  • perSecond(double)
  • perYear(double)

Rates can be compared with compareTo(Rate), isFasterThan(Rate) and isSlowerThan(Rate).

The method throttle(Rate) will delay (if this rate is greater than the given maximum) long enough to limit this rate to the maximum rate.

Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
